         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>229</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>83f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Derentwegen der Reichtum erworben [wtl. gesammelt] worden ist, (die) ... haben mich aus meinem eigenen Hau(se) verstoßen [wtl. herausgezogen].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Those for whose sake the wealth had been gathered, (they) ... have banned [lit. drawn] me from my own house.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>83-4, 439</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Um derentwillen der Reichtum erworben [wtl. gesammelt] worden ist, (die) ... haben mich (aus) meinem eigenen Hau(se) verstoßen [wtl. herausgezogen].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Those for whose sake the wealth had been gathered, (they) ... have banned [lit. drawn] me from my own house.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>245</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a11 #a12"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Bettelmönch ist man nicht insofern, als man andere anbettelt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">One is not a begging monk (mendicant) insofar as one begs of others.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>147</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a12"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>137</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>200</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// as a worn-out horse, unfed ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>337</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>7f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7 #a8 #a9"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Dieser Stock [ist] für mich besser als [wtl. nicht aber] die (ungeratenen) Söhne. Er hält eine wildgewordene Kuh fern und einen (bösartigen(?)) Hund.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">This stick [is] better for me than [lit. for me, but not] (undutiful) sons. It keeps away a cow gone wild and a (vicious(?)) dog.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>499</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... it [i.e. the stick] keeps away a cow that has been driven mad</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a9"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>96</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
